ct to the difficulty of finding a\ncosmological dipole. The lowest correlation upper limits we can place are about\n15 % of COBE CMB fluctuations and about 10 % of the ROSAT extragalactic XRB\nfluctuations. We discuss these results with respect to possible correlation\nmechanisms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Oct 1996 11:41:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
